---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import CTASection from '../../components/CTASection.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Case Studies"
  description="Real automation results from real engagements. See how ForgeRPA helps companies streamline operations and reduce costs."
  heroTitle="Results That Speak"
  heroSubtitle="Real outcomes from real engagements."
>
  <section class="py-20 lg:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 space-y-20">

      <!-- Case Study 1: Enterprise Data Analysis -->
      <article class="scroll-mt-24">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <span class="px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold bg-charcoal text-amber rounded-full">Enterprise</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-500">Data Analysis at Scale</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-charcoal mb-4">Enterprise Data Analysis Beyond Excel's Limits</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-amber-dark font-semibold mb-8">Deployed across multiple business units</p>

        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal mb-3">Challenge</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              A large manufacturer needed to analyze operational datasets that regularly exceeded Excel's worksheet row limits. The exported data was too large for standard Excel analysis, leaving teams unable to build the PivotTable reports they relied on for decision-making. Multiple business units faced the same limitation.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal mb-3">Approach</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              We designed a fully automated end-to-end solution. An RPA process extracted the data, used VBA within the automation to refresh Power Query connections and update PivotTable reports, then placed the finished file in SharePoint and emailed the folder link to users. The Data Model (Power Pivot) handled the heavy lifting with DAX measures for analysis, while PivotTables provided the familiar reporting interface teams already knew how to use. No new software. No additional licensing. No manual steps. Users simply received an email with their updated reports ready to go.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal mb-3">Outcome</h3>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
              {[
                'RPA orchestrated VBA, Power Query refresh, and SharePoint delivery',
                'End-to-end automation: extract, transform, publish, notify',
                'Full analysis of datasets beyond Excel row limits',
                'DAX-powered Data Model for advanced calculations',
                'Deployed across multiple business units',
                'Zero manual steps. Zero additional licensing.',
              ].map((item) => (
                <div class="flex items-start gap-2 text-gray-700">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-amber-dark flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                  </svg>
                  <span class="text-sm">{item}</span>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <hr class="border-gray-200" />

      <!-- Case Study 2: Month-End Close -->
      <article class="scroll-mt-24">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <span class="px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold bg-charcoal text-amber rounded-full">Finance</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-500">Month-End Close Automation</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-charcoal mb-4">40 Hours of Manual Work Reduced to Under 20 Minutes</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-amber-dark font-semibold mb-8">Replicated across multiple accounting groups with the same results</p>

        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal mb-3">Challenge</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              During month-end close, five team members each spent a full 8-hour day performing the same process for their assigned companies. The work involved downloading data from SAP, performing analysis, and preparing journal entries. Combined, this single process consumed over 40 hours every close cycle.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal mb-3">Approach</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              We built a full end-to-end automation. RPA handled the SAP downloads and ran advanced VBA to perform all the analysis, calculations, and journal entry preparation within Excel. The finished files were saved to SharePoint and users received an email notification with a direct link to their completed reports. No manual steps from start to finish. What previously required five people each working a full day was consolidated into a single automated process.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              This end-to-end pattern of RPA extraction, advanced Excel and VBA processing, SharePoint delivery, and email notification became one of our most effective and repeatable approaches and was replicated across multiple accounting groups with the same dramatic results.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-charcoal mb-3">Outcome</h3>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
              {[
                'Full E2E: SAP download to SharePoint delivery with email notification',
                'Advanced VBA handled all analysis and journal entry preparation',
                '40+ hours reduced to under 20 minutes',
                'Zero manual steps from start to finish',
                'Replicated across multiple accounting groups',
                'Same dramatic time savings in every group',
              ].map((item) => (
                <div class="flex items-start gap-2 text-gray-700">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-amber-dark flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                  </svg>
                  <span class="text-sm">{item}</span>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <hr class="border-gray-200" />

      <!-- More Case Studies Coming -->
      <div class="text-center">
        <div class="bg-slate-light rounded-xl p-12 lg:p-16">
          <div class="text-5xl mb-6">📋</div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-charcoal mb-4">More Case Studies Coming Soon</h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
            We are preparing additional case studies from our engagements across industries. Each will include the challenge, our approach, measurable outcomes, and lessons learned.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-6 text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
            Book a discovery call to hear how we have delivered results for companies like yours.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-8">
            <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 bg-amber hover:bg-amber-dark text-charcoal font-bold text-lg rounded-lg transition-colors shadow-lg shadow-amber/20">
              Book a Discovery Call
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <CTASection
    heading="Let Us Show You What's Possible"
    subtext="Book a free 30-minute discovery call. We will identify your top automation candidates and estimate the ROI."
    ctaText="Book a Discovery Call"
    ctaLink="/contact"
  />
</PageLayout>
